    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-01-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gibbs</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13,
                                1879</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 129.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your Nos. 215 and 268
                            touching the claim of Thomas W. Sparrow on Peru, I have to observe that
                            Mr. C. G. Lee, attorney for claimant, has lately addressed the
                            Department, urging that the matter be pressed on the attention of the
                            Peruvian Government. I have informed him that your last dispatch on the
                            subject gave reason to suppose that the claim would soon be settled.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. M. Evarts.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
